info.headline: Flood Warning issued July 10 at 2:15AM EDT until July 10 at 9:45AM EDT by NWS Baltimore MD/Washington DC
info.description:
* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is occurring.
* WHERE...A portion of northeast Maryland, including the following county, Cecil.
* WHEN...Until 945 AM EDT Thursday.
* IMPACTS...Flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations is imminent or occurring.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 213 AM EDT, local law enforcement reported flooding in the warned area. Flooding is already occurring. - High water has been reported in Elkton and other streams may be flooding as earlier heavy rainfall drains southward from Pennsylvania. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Elkton... Calvert... North East... Rising Sun... Zion... Bay View... Lombard... Farmington... Pleasant Hill... Blake... West Nottingham... Fair Hill... Andora... Cherry Hill... Barksdale... Richardsmere... Octoraro... Conowingo... - Please visit www.weather.gov/safety/flood for flood safety and preparedness information
info.instruction:
Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the dangers of flooding.

parameter.value: FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 945 AM EDT THIS MORNING
